The paper deals with a neural reading comprehension model that integrates external commonsense knowledge, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The model also involves machine learning techniques such as attention mechanisms and memory networks, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions improving results on a dataset, which suggests that it involves experimental evaluation, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category. Finally, the use of external knowledge sources and memory networks suggests that the paper may also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
